Undertaking to discharge liabilities

The [applicant] / [respondent] shall discharge as and when each payment becomes due, be solely responsible for and in any event indemnify the [respondent] / [applicant] against:

the premiums in respect of the [policy] / [endowment policy] / [pension policy] with [company] numbered [policy number];

the [monthly] repayments to [company] in respect of the hire purchase agreement with them numbered [agreement number] in respect of the [family car] / [car make and model] with registration number [reg. number];

the [monthly] repayments to [company] in respect of the loan agreement with them numbered [agreement number] in respect of [insert];

[etc].

The payments shall start on [date] and shall end on the first to occur of:

[date];

the sale of the family home;

the youngest surviving [of the] child[ren] of the family attaining the age of 18 years or ceasing [his] / [her] / [their] full-time [secondary] / [tertiary] education [to first degree level], or [permanently] ceasing to live with the [applicant] / [respondent], whichever is the later;

the [respondent’s] / [applicant’s] remarriage;

the death of either party;

the retirement of the [applicant] / [respondent];

a court order discharging this obligation;

[etc].

[(For avoidance of doubt, where the relevant child takes a pre-tertiary education gap year, delaying the commencement of tertiary education by one year, this shall not be construed as ceasing tertiary education.)]

Undertaking to pay extra-curricular child costs

The [applicant] / [respondent] shall discharge as and when each payment becomes due, be solely responsible for and in any event indemnify the [respondent] / [applicant] against the following extra-curricular expenses of the child[ren]:

[insert (e.g. non-school extra-curricular activities such as clubs, tuition, music lessons etc.)].

Undertaking to discharge arrears

